there are 3 cloud models ; public, private and hybrid
-Public requires no up-front costs and is shared among customer
-Private clouds are used by a single org only and require you to pay for the hardware and maintenance 
-A Hybrid cloud is the combination of public and private 


Availability zones are physically separate datacenters within an Azure region
Each availbility zone consists of the one or more datacanters with independent power, cooling, and networking 
Availability sets protect agabinst hardware failures within a datacenter, but availability zones protect against datacenter failures within a region 

Asubscription provides authenticated and authorized access to Azure products 
An Azure subscription is a logical unit of Azure service that links to an Azure account, which is an identuty in Azure Active Directory (Azure AD)
or in a directory that Azure AD trusts 

A subcription can be aa Billing boundary or an Access control boundary, and you can organize multiple subscriptions into different invoice 
sections by creating billing profiles

Azure management groups allow you to manage access, policies, and compliance for multiple subscription.
All subscriptions within a management group automatically inherit the conditions applied to the management group 
All subscriptions within a single management group must trust the same Azure AD tenant 

Review the hierarchy image 

A resource is a manageable item that's available through Azure. VMs, storage accounts, web apps, databases, and virtual network are example of resources 
A resource group is a container that holds related resources for an Azure solution. includes resources that yoy want to manage as a group 
